OSRSCN
======

The Simplified Chinese translation data shipped with this plugin is the transcript and
translation work of lck3141592654 (https://github.com/lck3141592654).

This plugin bundles a subset of the Source Han Sans SC font (version 2.005R,
https://github.com/adobe-fonts/source-han-sans) to render Chinese glyphs. The bundled file
(SourceHanSansSC-Regular.otf) is a derivative: it has been subset to the characters this plugin
needs, and (as required by the SIL Open Font License Reserved Font Name clause) its internal
font names no longer use the Reserved Font Name 'Source' (renamed to 'OSRSCN HanSans SC').
Original copyright © 2014-2025 Adobe (http://www.adobe.com/), with Reserved Font Name 'Source'.
Source is a trademark of Adobe in the United States and/or other countries. The font is licensed
under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1; the full license text is in OFL-1.1.txt (also bundled
in the JAR). The font is used for rendering only; OSRSCN itself remains under BSD 2-Clause (see LICENSE).

This product includes work derived from RuneLingual
(https://github.com/YS-jack/RuneLingual-Plugin), used under the BSD 2-Clause License.

Specifically, the <colNumN> colour-placeholder scheme used to match the community OSRS
transcript data — com.osrscn.text.Tags#placeholdColors / #colorTags / #restoreColors — follows
RuneLingual's com.RuneLingual.commonFunctions.Colors. The translation data format (English keys
storing colours as <colNum0>, <colNum1>, ... and numbers as <Num0>, <Num1>, ...) originates with
the RuneLingual project and the community transcript effort.

